	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=139867><span id= >trystdare</span></a><br><span id=notbold>24 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.94]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>After finally reaching level 45 you will be able to use your Jaundiced Bone bracer.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is a 263 Cold Based Direct Damage clickable effect with a casting time of 8 seconds and no recast time.  Other may vary but here is how I  have leveled with my JBB.<br><br>At 45 when I was able to use it my pet was easily devoured by mobs as we got higher in levels so I was more prone to use root/enstill as well as slow to help him survive longer.  I NEVER buffed myself with anything besides what my Jaundiced Armor could cast, bear form (for regen and wis buff) and Chloro (for regen) because I was neber meleed for more than a few hits and chloro would regain that while standing.  I would pull to pet, send pet, then blast.  I could normally get my JBB off 3 times before I drew agro.  When that happened I would just channel through a root/enstill and step back and pop off a couple more.  I think the max number of blasts I got off was 7 in one battle with the mob slowed and only rooted once.  Pet lost half life but was a big chunk of exp gained on a dark blue.<br><br>I have since then passed 49, recieved a new pet and my tactics are about the same.  I now only slow the mob when it is dark blue, the rest I can root and blast while my pet slowly eats at it.  Usually end up with full health, no mana spent (besides root) and pet at 3/4 health.<br><br>Your goal, of course, is to use no mana on these fights.  Practice with different mobs and different strategies.  You will find the one that works.  In short, I use from 2 - 4 enstills and get off about 4 - 7 JBB blasts.  Mana wise I still find it worth it to use just the JBB and root when soloing.  As mobs get more hitpoints I will most likely have to change my solo strategy.<br><br>And that is how I do it.  Hope my information helps you and anyone else.<br><br>Sequi Sicarius<br>49th Season and Climbing<br>Clan MacLear Shaman<br>Xegony</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
