	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2440><span id=Sage>Dargadin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>949 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Some points...<br><br>1) Slow will reduce the speed with which they hit you, not the speed that they run. The good thing aobut this is it gives you more time between hits to cast a root.<br><br>2) If you can keep the MoB rooted, then just nuke, nuke, nuke with the JBB. That consumes very little mana.<br><br>3) Your pet will attack if you are hit anyway.<br><br>Personally, I send in the pet first to distract the mob while I get my debuffs and root off, then I recall the pet once the mob is rooted.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Mob gets a chance to break  root every 6 seconds AND every time it gets hit, so if oyu are slamming him with a JBB, don't bother with Enstill, just use Root.<br><br>The JBB does take some time to cast, but since it uses no mana it just becomes a matter of keeping him rooted.<br><br>Of course, this won't work on Ice Giants :)</p>&nbsp;<br>______________________________________<br><b>Dargadin, Barbarian Shaman of the 61st Season</b><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=494767" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=494767</a><br><b><span style='color: red;'>Lost Fires</span style='color: red;'><br>Ayonae Ro Server</b><br></td></td></tr>
